\pard\f0\fs28 Herbs, shrubs or woody climbers, often with swollen nodes. Leaves simple, entire, exstipulate. Flowers solitary or in small, terminal umbels (rarely in whorls), subtended by bracts which often simulate a perianth. Perianth petaloid, tubular, with a short, 5-lobed limb; lower part of tube persistent and concrescent with the fruit to form an achene-like anthocarp. Stamens usually 3-5. Ovary superior, 1-celled, containing a single ovule.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Various cultivars and hybrids of {\i Bougainvillea,} woody climbers with alternate leaves and an involucre of 3 conspicuous, brightly coloured bracts, are extensively planted for ornament in parts of the Mediterranean region.
