\pard\f0\fs28 Shrubs or somewhat woody herbs with opposite leaves. Flowers small, in whorls or umbels. Bracts few and inconspicuous. Perianth-tube contracted above the ovary and surmounted by a spreading, 5-lobed limb. Stamens 1-6. Anthocarp with distinct longitudinal ribs, glandular, viscid.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. B. repens} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 3 (1753). Plant glandular-pubescent, viscid; rather woody. Stems up to 100 cm, decumbent to ascending, much-branched. Leaves 5-25(-50) mm, ovate to elliptical, with sinuate margins; petiole about as long as the lamina. Flowers in rather dense, 4- to 10-flowered umbels on peduncles 1-2 cm. Perianth 2·5-3 mm, pink or purple. Stamens 2. Anthocarp 3-4 mm, clavate. {\i Naturalized as a ruderal in Sicilia} ({\i Palermo}). [Si.] ({\i Tropical Africa and Asia.})
\par

